# Component Development Rules — CSS-First Architecture

## Step 1: SCSS Component (`packages/css-components/`)

ALL visual styles go here first. This is the single source of truth.

```scss
// _component-name.scss — BEM naming with configurable prefix
.{prefix}-component {
  display: flex;
  padding: var(--vcds-spacing-md);
  background: var(--vcds-color-surface-primary);
  border-radius: var(--vcds-radius-md);
  font-family: var(--vcds-font-family-sans);

  &:focus-visible {
    outline: none;
    box-shadow: var(--vcds-focus-ring);
  }
}

.{prefix}-component--primary { /* variant */ }
.{prefix}-component--sm { /* size */ }
.{prefix}-component__header { /* sub-element */ }
```

After creating, register: `@use 'components/component-name';` in `src/index.scss`

## Step 2: HTML Reference (`packages/html/examples/`)

Create a standalone HTML page showing all variants with BEM classes. No JS required.

## Step 3: Framework Wrappers (thin — NO styles)

### React (`packages/react/`)

```tsx
// Thin wrapper — maps props to BEM classes. NO CSS imports, NO style files.
import { forwardRef } from 'react';
import type { ComponentProps } from './Component.types';

export const Component = forwardRef<HTMLElement, ComponentProps>(
  ({ variant = 'default', size = 'md', className, children, ...rest }, ref) => {
    const classNames = [
      '{prefix}-component',
      `{prefix}-component--${variant}`,
      `{prefix}-component--${size}`,
      className ?? '',
    ].filter(Boolean).join(' ');

    return (
      <element ref={ref} className={classNames} {...rest}>
        {children}
      </element>
    );
  }
);
Component.displayName = 'Component';
```

### Vue (`packages/vue/`)

```vue
<!-- Thin wrapper — NO <style> block -->
<script setup lang="ts">
withDefaults(defineProps<{ variant?: string; size?: string }>(), {
  variant: 'default', size: 'md',
});
defineOptions({ name: 'DsComponent' });
</script>

<template>
  <element :class="['{prefix}-component', `{prefix}-component--${variant}`, `{prefix}-component--${size}`]">
    <slot />
  </element>
</template>
<!-- No <style> — all styles come from @vcds/css-components -->
```

### Svelte (`packages/svelte/`)

```svelte
<!-- Thin wrapper — NO <style> block -->
<script lang="ts">
  let { variant = 'default', size = 'md', children, ...rest }: Props = $props();
</script>

<element class="{prefix}-component {prefix}-component--{variant} {prefix}-component--{size}" {...rest}>
  {@render children?.()}
</element>
<!-- No <style> — all styles come from @vcds/css-components -->
```

## Shared Rules (All Frameworks)

- ALWAYS start with SCSS in `packages/css-components/` — CSS-first
- ALWAYS create HTML reference page before framework wrappers
- Framework wrappers MUST NOT contain `<style>` blocks, CSS Modules, or style imports
- ALWAYS use BEM classes: `.{prefix}-{component}`, `.{prefix}-{component}--{variant}`
- ALWAYS use semantic tokens via `var(--vcds-*)` — no hardcoded values
- ALWAYS include ARIA attributes and keyboard handling
- ALWAYS create a types file with exported interface
- ALWAYS write tests with axe-core assertions
- ALWAYS create Storybook stories for all variants and states
- ALWAYS provide a `className`/`class` prop for composition
